Example

This is a basic example which shows you how to solve a common problem:

library(pathways)
library(dplyr)
library(DOSE)
library(pathways)
library(tidyverse)
library(igraph)
library(ggraph)
load(system.file("data", "Tes.Rdata", package = "pathways"))
n@kegg_analyst$compareClusterResult@compareClusterResult %>%
    dplyr::filter(org == "KEGG") %>%
    dplyr::filter((Description %in% c((n@kegg_analyst$compareClusterResult@compareClusterResult %>%
        group_by(Description) %>%
        summarise(n = n() > 1)) %>%
        dplyr::filter(n == T) %>%
        .$Description) | qvalue < 0.05)) %>%
    as.data.frame() -> f
circos.clear()
circos.par(cell.padding = c(0, 0, 0, 0), points.overflow.warning = FALSE, start.degree = 90)
plot_chor(f, metaProfiler = n) -> v
pd = packLegend(list = v)
draw(pd, x = unit(1, "cm"), y = unit(1, "cm"), just = c("left", "bottom"))

comp_dotplot(n@kegg_analyst$enrichKEGG$a)

n@kegg_analyst$enrichKEGG$a -> lllll
lllll -> da
da@result %>%
    dplyr::filter(org == "KEGG") -> y
